From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lpo build fix <noreply@example.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] unzip: remove obsolete gmtime/localtime redeclarations

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [toolchain-specific compatibility fix]

Modern libc headers provide prototypes with typed arguments:
- gmtime(const time_t *)
- localtime(const time_t *)

The legacy declaration in unix/unxcfg.h uses K&R-style empty argument
lists, which now conflicts with the standard declarations and fails the
build on newer toolchains.

---
 unix/unxcfg.h | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/unix/unxcfg.h b/unix/unxcfg.h
index fa200ce..ccdb7d7 100644
--- a/unix/unxcfg.h
+++ b/unix/unxcfg.h
@@ -117,7 +117,6 @@
 #  endif
 #else
 #  include <time.h>
-   struct tm *gmtime(), *localtime();
 #endif
 
 #if (defined(BSD4_4) || (defined(SYSV) && defined(MODERN)))
-- 
2.43.0
